The paper discusses lattice reduction algorithms and their application in designing integer-forcing linear receivers for multi-input multioutput communications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes improvements to the KZ and LLL algorithms, which are commonly used in computational number theory and optimization, respectively. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Systems and Control (cs.SY), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
